\par\pard\plain \li540\fi-270\sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch \ls1\ilvl0{\listtext	\f5\fs26\b1\i0 1.	}{\f5\fs26\b1\i0 Retain Dialogue Verbatim:}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  All dialogue provided must be incorporated exactly as written. Each line of dialogue is crucial to preserving the characters' voices and the narrative flow.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f5\fs26\b1\i0 2.	}{\f5\fs26\b1\i0 Retain All lines of Dialogue:}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  Ensure that every line of dialogue provided is included in the scene without omissions. It's crucial that none of the dialogue lines are left out to maintain the integrity and continuity of the narrative.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f5\fs26\b1\i0 3.	}{\f5\fs26\b1\i0 Action Tags and Dialogue Tags:}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  Surround the provided dialogue with compelling action tags, dialogue tags, and narrative enhancements based on instructions within brackets or parentheses. These instructions are meant to guide you in conveying the tone of the speaker, emotional context, and specific actions or descriptions.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f5\fs26\b1\i0 4.	}{\f5\fs26\b1\i0 Narrative Flexibility:}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  While dialogue must remain unchanged, you have the freedom to modify, delete, or add to narrative paragraphs provided. Use these as a rough draft to craft more polished narrative content.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f5\fs26\b1\i0 5.	}{\f5\fs26\b1\i0 Use Simple Past Tense:}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  Write all scenes using simple past tense to maintain consistency in narrative voice.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f5\fs26\b1\i0 6.	}{\f5\fs26\b1\i0 Immersive Storytelling:}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  Avoid meta-references to the 'scene' or the writing process within the narrative itself. Keep the reader fully immersed in the story.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f5\fs26\b1\i0 7.	}{\f5\fs26\b1\i0 Emphasis on "Showing" Over "Telling":}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  Use descriptive imagery and action to show what's happening in the scene, rather than simply telling. Deep POV (Point of View) should be employed to immerse the reader in the characters' experiences and emotions.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f5\fs26\b1\i0 8.	}{\f5\fs26\b1\i0 Internal Dialogue Formatting:}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  Use italics instead of quotes for internal dialogue to clearly differentiate characters' thoughts from spoken words.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f5\fs26\b1\i0 9.	}{\f5\fs26\b1\i0 Dialogue Writing Convention:}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  Adhere to standard dialogue writing conventions by starting a new paragraph with every change of speaker, enhancing readability and clarity.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f5\fs26\b1\i0 10.	}{\f5\fs26\b1\i0 Dialogue Naturalness:}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  Use contractions in character dialogue to reflect natural speech patterns and enhance realism.}
