\par\pard\plain \tx0\fi360\sa120\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f5\fs26\b1\i0\cf8 <$Scr_Cs::4>Evan<!$Scr_Cs::4>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f6\fs26\b0\i1\cf9 <$Scr_Cs::5>(distressed and concerned):<!$Scr_Cs::5>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I don\u8217\'92t understand why you had to go back to your maiden name so quickly or why you stopped wearing your wedding ring before the divorce was finalized. I still have mine on. Are you already in the market looking for someone else?\u8221\'94}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\fi360\sa120\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 <$Scr_Ps::6>Sarah\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s silence and body language spoke volumes as she looked down in shame. Her response gave Evan his answer. Evan felt like he just got a giant punch in the stomach. He buried his face into his hands in distress.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Wanting to console Evan, Sarah walked over to Evan\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s side of the table. She squatted down and spun his chair in her direction. <!$Scr_Ps::6>}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\fi360\sa120\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f5\fs26\b1\i0\cf8 <$Scr_Cs::4>Sarah<!$Scr_Cs::4>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f6\fs26\b0\i1\cf9 <$Scr_Cs::5>(Compassionate, wanting to clarify):<!$Scr_Cs::5>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Evan, I don\u8217\'92t want to hurt you. I\u8217\'92m back in college, working towards my master\u8217\'92s degree, and I was collaborating on a project with a guy near my age. We are the oldest ones in the class, and we bonded. We went on a couple of dates, but nothing happened, Evan. Not even a kiss.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f5\fs26\b1\i0\cf8 <$Scr_Cs::4>Sarah<!$Scr_Cs::4>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f6\fs26\b0\i1\cf9 <$Scr_Cs::5>(continuing with honesty):<!$Scr_Cs::5>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I explained to him the situation. He knows he and I can only be friends for now. I am focused on my degree, and I doubt anything will come of that relationship. Please look at me.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f6\fs26\b0\i1\cf9 <$Scr_Cs::5>[ Evan struggled to look at Sarah, but finally found the strength. He felt hurt more than anger. Evan is recovering, but still reeling a bit from the revelation that Sarah went on a date with another man. However, that realization seems to have cemented in his mind that indeed his relationship with Sarah is ending. ]<!$Scr_Cs::5>}
